		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=1286"><span id="Sage">gbaji</span></a><b><span id="Sage"><br>Encyclopedia</span></b><br /><span style="font-size:9px;color: red;">There is no 5th star.</span><br />10511 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.02]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=gbaji&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p><blockquote><b class="sm">czaemon wrote:</b><hr size="1" /><blockquote><b class="sm">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />4. Paladin- why the heck aren't they adding new stuns and paci? <hr size="1" /></blockquote> <br />I'm actually still kind of confused *what* paladins complain about stun-wise.&nbsp;&nbsp;is it just that there aren't enough to-70 stuns to chainstun a mob?<hr size="1" /></blockquote> <br /> <br />It's not that paladins complain about out stun spells (at least I don't). What we complain about is that other classes perception of the relative power of our stuns is much greater then they actually are. If you recall the last time we discussed this, I responded specifically to someone posting that paladin stuns increased in power at the higher level, when in fact they have been decreased over time as we level past 55. <br /> <br />I happen to think that our stuns are about right in power. The problem is that since the perception of the power of those stuns is higher then their actual power, paladins are often overlooked in other aspects of class balancing, often resulting in us being left in the dust. <br /> <br />Look at it another way. A kiting class can spend a relatively small amount of mana one time on a snare and effectively avoid all damage from any non-summoning mob (within a reasonable level range of course). How exactly is being able to have to spend 60-80 mana every 4-5 seconds over the course of the fight to do the exact same thing unbalancing? It isn't. Not if you really stop and think about it. A paladin with all his spells and sufficient AA points spent can effectively stun lock mobs (not easily, but it can be done). It just costs him a ton of mana to do. <br /> <br />When you add in the fact that a paladin's dps is about as crappy as any in the game, this becomes a huge problem. There are tons of mobs out there that I don't bother to fight solo simply because their dps is higher then I can mitigate with my heals, and I'll run out of mana for stuns before I can kill the mob with damage. Even the range of mobs below that are less then prime because while I can kill them, I'll blow significant amounts of mana in the process, resulting in large amounts of downtime between kills. <br /> <br />In a group tanking setting, paladin stuns work just fine. But they are *not* a balance to other classes abilities across the board. But many people think of them that way and assume we don't need any other help. That's where the problem lies IMO...</p>
</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from San Diego, CA</td></tr></table>
