		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=1286"><span id="Sage">gbaji</span></a><b><span id="Sage"><br>Encyclopedia</span></b><br /><span style="font-size:9px;color: red;">There is no 5th star.</span><br />10511 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.02]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=gbaji&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p><blockquote><b class="sm">czaemon wrote:</b><hr size="1" />how have they decreased in power post-55?&nbsp;&nbsp;going off procs from weaps, there are very few stun immune mobs.<hr size="1" /></blockquote> <br /> <br />Huh? The fact that at level 54, we had 5 stuns (requiring no questing or difficulty to obtain) that could affect any mob from 1 to 7 levels *higher* then our own level, and at level 70, we have *2* spells that can affect mobs our level or lower, and 2 more that can as well (one of which requires expending 30AA points to make it about as effective relatively as any of the spells we had at level 54, and the other is an &quot;ancient&quot; line spell from OoW). <br /> <br />Stun spell durations on the &quot;normal&quot; stuns reduce from 6 seconds to 4 seconds (that's a 33% reduction right there, right?). <br /> <br />So, at absolute best case, we lose 20% of the spells we had. Half of those are additionally reduced in duration by 33%. The math is really straightforward Czae. It's not about how many stun immune mobs there are (although there certainly are more at level 70 then at level 55, right?). It's a straight reduction in the number and relative quality of the spells we get (and greater difficulty to obtain to boot, although all classes get that). <br /> <br />It's a straight reduction in power across the board. No other solution. But your reaction is typical of the playerbase as a whole. Even after pointing out the numbers, they still don't believe that our ability to stun has been reduced.  <br /> <br />That's the problem with our stuns. Everyone thinks that they are as powerful, or in some cases *more* powerful at level 70 then they were at level 55, causing us to get screwed when class balancing time comes along.</p>
