<p><blockquote><b class="sm">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />Huh? The fact that at level 54, we had 5 stuns (requiring no questing or difficulty to obtain) that could affect any mob from 1 to 7 levels *higher* then our own level, and at level 70, we have *2* spells that can affect mobs our level or lower, and 2 more that can as well (one of which requires expending 30AA points to make it about as effective relatively as any of the spells we had at level 54, and the other is an &quot;ancient&quot; line spell from OoW)<hr size="1" /></blockquote> <br />note: <br /><blockquote><b class="sm">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />is it just that there aren't enough to-70 stuns to chainstun a mob?<hr size="1" /></blockquote> <br /> <br /><blockquote><b class="sm">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />No other solution. But your reaction is typical of the playerbase as a whole. Even after pointing out the numbers, they still don't believe that our ability to stun has been reduced.<hr size="1" /></blockquote> <br />if the general reaction to seeing someone saying paladin spells decreased in power is asking how they decreased, then paladin balance would be in pretty good hands.  <br /> <br /> <br /> <br />until your last post, you *didn't* point out any numbers.  <br /> <br />But your reaction is typical of the paladinbase as a whole. Even before pointing out the numbers, they&nbsp;&nbsp;believe that the general playerbase is out to get them.  <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Fri Apr  1 22:20:35 2005 by czaemon</span></i></p>
