		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=247125"><span id="Scholar">Jiggidyjay of the Seven Seas</span></a><b><span id="Scholar"><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img alt="Avatar" height="98" width="77" src="/uf/Jiggidyjay/ava4.jpg"><br /><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />1906 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.52]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Jiggidyjay&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>While I see your frustration Gbaji, I can't say I really feel that sympathetic. Every class has their big problems, especially any caster class. I can tell you that being a bard in the high end can be very annoying. I know you probably don't want to hear about bard problems, but I'm gonna tell you anyway <img border="0" src="/shared/smilies/sly.gif" alt="icon"/>. <br /> <br />At level 65 the typical bard will have <a href="HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/spell.html?spell=4112" title="HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/spell.html?spell=4112" target="akztarg">Call of Muse</a>, which is 15% DD/Dot focus, 30% overhaste, max level 65 (10% reduction each level over cap). Remember that that reduction is based on the person it's focusing/overhasting, not the bard. Some bards, if doing enough GoD, will have Trusik, which is 25% spell focus/30% overhaste. <br /> <br />We get our next upgrade at 68, <a href="HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/spell.html?spell=5380" title="HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/spell.html?spell=5380" target="akztarg">Yelhun's Mystic Call</a>. It's 15%/30%, max level 70 and is the 3rd rune turn in. So, we've lost 30% effectiveness off of our level 65 song, get the upgrade, and it's the same thing as our level 65 song. <br /> <br />At 69, we get Eriki's, which is the same as Trusik, 25%/30%, max level 70. Lost 40% of our level 65 songs effectiveness in this case, to get it back to what it was. <br /> <br />Then, care to guess what our level 70 ancient is? Yes, an upgrade to these songs, a 30%/30%, max level 70, yay! <br /> <br />Now, I'm not saying pally's didn't get screwed somewhere, because they very well may have. I'm just pointing out that in the grand scheme of things, most people don't care what &quot;plights&quot; other classes go through, because they're too worried about their own, and you know the grass is always greener on the other side. It's just too easy for people to say &quot;X class is just fine as it is, worry about us more!&quot; and that's what most do, correct or not.</p>
