		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=1286"><span id="Sage">gbaji</span></a><b><span id="Sage"><br>Encyclopedia</span></b><br /><span style="font-size:9px;color: red;">There is no 5th star.</span><br />10511 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.02]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=gbaji&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p><blockquote><b class="sm">czaemon wrote:</b><hr size="1" /><blockquote><b class="sm">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />(even though I went over all of this in detail like 3 weeks ago in another thread that you were involved in)<hr size="1" /></blockquote> <br />you went over general paladin problems, and whined that your stun power had been reduced, but you never actually said *how* <br /> <br />I really was just curious -- I've never looked at paladin post-55 spell lines in detail.<hr size="1" /></blockquote> <br /> <br />Hmmm... Ok. I just assumed since you replied to <a href="HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/forum.html?forum=1&amp;mid=1110468099644988581&amp;num=36" title="HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/forum.html?forum=1&amp;mid=1110468099644988581&amp;num=36" target="akztarg">this thread</a> after I posted this info, that you'd actually read it. <br /> <br />But for your own edification, here's the relevent bit again: <br /> <br /><blockquote><b class="sm">gbaji wrote:</b><hr size="1" /> <br /><pre> NAME&nbsp;&nbsp;                    LEVEL   SEC/Levelaffected  Notes   Stun                         30     4/55 Holy Might                   49     6/55 <span class="sm">damage</span> Force                        52     6/55 <span class="sm">damage</span> Force of Akera               53     4/61 Quelious Word of Tranquility 54    10/61 <span class="sm">damage,knockback</span>  Force of Akilae              62     4/65 Quelious Word of Serenity    64    10/65 <span class="sm">damage,knockback</span> <b>Ancient Force of Chaos       65     4/65</b>  Force of Piety               66     4/70 Serene Command               68    10/70 <span class="sm">damage,knockback</span> <b>Ancient Force of Jeron       70     4/70</b> </pre><hr size="1" /></blockquote> <br /> <br />I actually left out 2 stuns. The AA &quot;divine stun&quot; works on mobs up to level 65. It has a base recast of 30 seconds though, and so requires more AAs to reduce that (3 levels of 7 second reduction, giving you a final recast of 9 seconds). A second upgrade &quot;Celestial stun&quot; replaces it and affects mobs up to level 70. <br /> <br />Note that the last two &quot;sets&quot; of stuns are all linked. So the level 70 varients all replace the similarly named level 65 varient. <br /> <br />The point being that at those levels, a paladin has an absolute maximum of 4 stuns that can affect mobs in that level range. And only two of those are plain old spells. Of those two, the damage/knockback line *cannot* be used to chain since the recast is too long. <br /> <br />A level 54 paladin has 5 stuns that will affect mobs up to 55th level (and two that will work up to level 61, 7 levels higher then the paladins own level!). At level 65, that same paladin has 3 that affect up to his level (one of which is a ancient line though). He's got two more that affect mobs up to level 61 though, which isn't too bad (spells aren't linked yet, and you *might* occasionally fight mobs in a group that'll be low enough). <br /> <br />At level 70, that same paladin still has only 3 stuns. Again, only one easily obtainable stun that can be chained (so really no abilty to chain at all!). Back when he was 65, he could at least use force of akera and force of akilae and do a short chain (but not lock anything down). But odds are at level 70, he's not going to fight anything in a group that's level 61 or lower. <br /> <br />Point is that even if a level 70 paladin has obtained every single one of his stuns (including spending all the AAs possible on stuns and getting the level 70 ancient spell), he still has less relative stunning ability against level 70 mobs then he had against level 55 mobs when he was level 55. <br /> <br />That is a direct reduction in stunning power. We have fewer stuns. They last for shorter duration. They cost *more* mana (decrease in mana efficiency for effect, unlike many other spell lines which get *more* mana efficient as you gain levels). And they are harder to obtain (yes. I'm aware that all spells are harder to get, but requriing an ancient rune just to be able to maintain something close to the stun ability we had 15 levels earlier? Ridiculous). <br /> <br /> <br />Look at the numbers. Draw you own conclusions. Like I said earlier, I don't think that pally stuns are necessarily underpowered (I actually think they were overpowered in the 50s). I do think that the perception of the value of pally stuns is greater then the actual value though. There really is a belief by many players (and I suspect many devs) that they've kept up in power, or have gotten more powerful, and that most certainly colors any discussion of class balancing.</p>
